Failing the transfer via `markFailed` upon receiving a chunk with an invalid token or sender ID introduces a denial-of-service (DoS) vulnerability. If a transfer ID is guessed or leaked, an attacker could send a malicious chunk to terminate a legitimate export. Instead of failing the entire transfer, these invalid requests should be ignored and logged. The transfer will then naturally expire via the TTL mechanism if the legitimate client has disconnected.

